    "body": "Very good point about the fungible vs non-fungible (with respect to time) gas costs.  It is an interesting idea to have some mechanism by which you can explicitly ensure that storage space is *not* being used during off-peak and then use that storage space during on-peak.  One can imagine an account being initialized with a \"new storage slot creation\" counter (20,000 gas initialization cost) and then paying `20,000 * num_purchased + 5000` gas to \"bank\" a number of new storage slot writes.  Then during on-peak they could redeem those tokens for new storage slot writes instead of using gas like normal (they would still have to pay 5000 for the counter update).  You could have a similar counter for banked storage slot updates as well (5000 each) and for contract creation (pay per byte).\r\n\r\nCertainly not a trivial proposal, but I don't think it is out of the realm of possibility.",
