    "body": "What is the use case for storing just state_size? Why not have the gas cost of storage be fixed since it doesn't matter when it is used i.e.\r\n\r\ntotal_gas_cost = (gas_used * gas_cost) + (storage_gas_used * fixed_storage_gas_cost)\r\n\r\nFurthermore, why not have a different cost for all network resources. For example, why not lower the cost of a transaction that uses a lot of CPU but not very much bandwidth if it's in a block with transactions that use lots of bandwidth and not very much CPU? i.e.\r\n\r\ntotal_gas_cost = (CPU_gas_used * CPU_gas_cost) + (bandwidth_gas_used * bandwidth_gas_cost) + (storage_gas_used * storage_gas_cost)\r\n",
