    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "It becomes very difficult to appropriately sort transactions when there are multiple dimensions to sort by.  Also, miners care much less about long term state growth but a lot more about uncle risk, so they may be incentivized to include transactions that pay very low (maybe 0) for state writes but very high network utilization gas prices.\r\n\r\nPerhaps we could manage state growth through an EIP-1559 like mechanism alone though?  We have some target state growth rate, and a base fee that adjusts up/down based on how much the user wants to write and miners can basically just ignore that since it doesn't significantly impact their uncle risk (maybe we would have a small regular gas charge for state writes to account for processing time costs).",
